# Staging before production (website + bot)

Ship work to **staging** by default. **Production** only when the user explicitly asks (e.g. “push to production”, “ship to prod”, “promote to live”).

| | Staging (default) | Production (user request only) |
|---|---|---|
| Website | **https://staging.pokepon.org** | **https://pokepon.org** |
| Website git | `staging` branch → `pokepon-org-staging` | `main` on `hamiebrooklyn.github.io` |
| API | `https://api-staging.pokepon.org` | `https://api.pokepon.org` |
| Bot | `scripts/start-bot-staging.sh` / `deploy-mac-staging.sh` | `scripts/deploy-mac.sh` |

Setup: `docs/WEBSITE_STAGING.md` (website) and `~/Developer/Poke-Cards/docs/STAGING.md` (bot).

## Agent workflow (every feature / fix)

1. **Code** on the website **`staging`** branch and in Poke-Cards (bot/API) as needed.
2. **Restart staging bot** after bot/API changes (you run it in the background — do not ask the user):
   ```bash
   cd ~/Developer/Poke-Cards
   bash scripts/start-bot-staging.sh
   ```
3. **Push to the staging website** (required when website files changed — this is the default “ship”):
   ```bash
   cd ~/Documents/GitHub/hamiebrooklyn.github.io
   git checkout staging
   bash scripts/deploy-website-staging.sh
   ```
   - Commits on `staging`, pushes `origin staging`, syncs **`pokepon-org-staging`** (updates **staging.pokepon.org**).
   - Does **not** push `main` or change **pokepon.org**.
4. **Tell the user** staging is ready: **https://staging.pokepon.org** (and staging bot if API changed).
5. **Stop here** unless the user asked for production in the same message.

## Push to production (only when the user says so)

Run these **only** after an explicit user request to push/promote/deploy **production** / **live** / **pokepon.org**:

**Website:**
```bash
cd ~/Documents/GitHub/hamiebrooklyn.github.io
bash scripts/promote-website-to-production.sh
```
(or merge `staging` → `main` and `git push origin main` — same outcome).

**Bot:**
```bash
cd ~/Developer/Poke-Cards
bash scripts/deploy-mac.sh
```

Confirm staging was tested before promoting unless the user explicitly skips staging.

## Do not

- Push `main` or run `promote-website-to-production.sh` without the user asking for production.
- Run `deploy-mac.sh` or restart production bot for routine feature work.
- Treat “done” as production-deployed — default “done” is **staging website pushed** + staging bot restarted.
- Ask the user to restart the staging bot — restart it yourself.
- Use `pokepon.org/?api=` as the primary test URL — use **staging.pokepon.org**.

## Do not confuse with git commit rules

- **Staging website push** (`deploy-website-staging.sh`) is part of finishing feature work — do it even if the user did not say “commit” (the script commits on `staging` when needed).
- **Production website push** still requires the user to say **push to production** (or equivalent).

Bot docs: `~/Developer/Poke-Cards/docs/STAGING.md`.
